                                                                                            <div class="title">
                                                    <span></span>
                                                    <h3>Erica & Mike - Parents of Rory (Alumni) & Pascale (Y3 Student)</h3>
                                                </div>
                                                                                    </div>
                                    </div>
                                                                    <div class="record-item">
                                        <div class="left">
                                            <div class="thumbnail bg-colour1">
                                                <span></span>
                                                <img src="/cache/img/019728165d4bf9b2c92b6b4c0a3150eb.png" alt="Untitled design (3)" loading="lazy" width="548" height="548" />                                            </div>
                                                                                            <div class="slider-pager">
                                                    <button class="prev"></button>
                                                    <span>2 / 3</span>
                                                    <button class="next"></button>
                                                </div>
                                                                                    </div>
                                        <div class="right">
                                            <article>
                                                                                                    <div class="content">
                                                        <p class="description">I am a proud parent of an alumnus and current student at Peak School. When we moved to Hong Kong we were looking for a small community school, and when we found Peak School, we looked no further. My children are excited to go to school every morning and come back home happy and full of joyful stories. Instead of homework, the focus is on the children to foster a love for reading, a key attribute of lifelong learners.This is cultivated by daily reading logs, library time, read alouds, author visits, and book week. Even the busy Principal finds the time to listen to stories read by new readers every week! Every child is met where they are at and there is no academic pressure. The teaching staff is caring and thoughtful. My older child is now in secondary school and thriving. The confidence, collaborative, and leadership skills she developed at Peak School has served her well, and the transition from a nurturing environment to a more rigorous one was relatively seamless.</p>
                                                        <button class="view-more">
                                                            <span>View More</span>
                                                        </button>
                                                        <p class="content">I am a proud parent of an alumnus and current student at Peak School. When we moved to Hong Kong we were looking for a small community school, and when we found Peak School, we looked no further. My children are excited to go to school every morning and come back home happy and full of joyful stories. Instead of homework, the focus is on the children to foster a love for reading, a key attribute of lifelong learners.This is cultivated by daily reading logs, library time, read alouds, author visits, and book week. Even the busy Principal finds the time to listen to stories read by new readers every week! Every child is met where they are at and there is no academic pressure. The teaching staff is caring and thoughtful. My older child is now in secondary school and thriving. The confidence, collaborative, and leadership skills she developed at Peak School has served her well, and the transition from a nurturing environment to a more rigorous one was relatively seamless.</p>
