                        </div>
                                    </div>
                            <div class="tab-content" data-id="3">
                                            <div class="record-slider">
                            <div class="slider-container">
                                                                    <div class="record-item">
                                        <div class="left">
                                            <div class="thumbnail bg-colour1">
                                                <span></span>
                                                <img src="/cache/img/84b1b90df17611a9583ff38caf9274ba.jpeg" alt="Katie Etchells-Bailey" loading="lazy" width="548" height="548" />                                            </div>
                                                                                            <div class="slider-pager">
                                                    <button class="prev"></button>
                                                    <span>1 / 3</span>
                                                    <button class="next"></button>
                                                </div>
                                                                                    </div>
                                        <div class="right">
                                            <article>
                                                                                                    <div class="content">
                                                        <p class="description">I have very happy memories of my six years spent at Peak School. I made lifelong friends who often remark on how lucky we were to have attended Peak. The Upper Playground, which still looks very similar today, was a highlight of each day; a huge space that invited children to play, explore, make up games and run freely. The community was an intimate and caring one and we felt safe and supported, allowing us to learn and flourish as individuals. We may not have had air con in the classrooms back in those days but there were plenty of smiles and happy memories made. I am proud to now be a Peak School parent, as my son embarks on his own Peak journey.</p>
                                                        <button class="view-more">
                                                            <span>View More</span>
                                                        </button>
